<TITLE> Aide to Iraq's Sadr says truce still in place </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 NAJAF, Iraq, March 26 (bdnews24.com/Reuters) - A ceasefire ordered by Iraqi cleric Moqtada al-Sadr remains in effect despite a crackdown on his followers in the southern city of Basra by government forces, a top aide said on Wednesday. "The freeze that Sadr has ordered is still ongoing," one of Sadr's senior aides, Luwaa Sumaisem, told Reuters in the Shi'ite holy city of Najaf.
